# Azure User Compliance Checker

A PowerShell script that connects to Microsoft Graph and identifies non-compliant users in your Azure Active Directory tenant.

---

## What It Checks

| Check | Description |
|---|---|
| **Sign-in disabled** | User account has been disabled |
| **No licence** | User has no assigned Microsoft licence |
| **Password never expires** | User's password policy is set to never expire |
| **MFA not registered** | User has not registered a second authentication method |

> **Note:** Sign-in activity (stale/inactive accounts) checks are not included as they require an Azure AD Premium licence.

---

## Requirements

- Azure Cloud Shell (PowerShell mode)
- The following PowerShell modules:
  - `Microsoft.Graph.Authentication`
  - `Microsoft.Graph.Users`
- An account with one of the following Azure roles:
  - **Global Administrator**
  - **Global Reader**
  - **Security Reader**

---

## Permissions Required

The script requests the following Microsoft Graph scopes on sign-in:

- `User.Read.All`
- `UserAuthenticationMethod.Read.All`

---

## How to Run

### Step 1 — Open Azure Cloud Shell
Go to [portal.azure.com](https://portal.azure.com) or directly to [shell.azure.com](https://shell.azure.com) and select **PowerShell**.

### Step 2 — Install Modules (first time only)
```powershell
Install-Module Microsoft.Graph.Authentication, Microsoft.Graph.Users -Scope CurrentUser -Force
```

### Step 3 — Open the Editor
Click the **{}** icon in the Cloud Shell toolbar, create a new file, paste the script, and save it as `compliance.ps1`.

### Step 4 — Run the Script
```powershell
./compliance.ps1
```
Sign in with your admin account when prompted.

### Step 5 — Download Results
When complete, download the CSV using the **⬆⬇** button in the Cloud Shell toolbar and enter `non-compliant-users.csv`.

---

## Output

The script produces a CSV file (`non-compliant-users.csv`) with the following columns:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| `Name` | User's display name |
| `UPN` | User Principal Name (email address) |
| `Issues` | Comma-separated list of compliance issues found |

---

## Limitations

- Requires **no Azure AD Premium licence** — works on standard tenants
- MFA check is done **per user** which may be slower on large tenants (100+ users)

---

## Troubleshooting

| Error | Fix |
|---|---|
| `403 Forbidden` on `Get-MgUser` | Your account may lack sufficient role permissions |
| `Module not found` | Re-run the `Install-Module` step |
| `Connect-MgGraph` hangs | Allow popups in your browser |
| Empty results | Check that your account has `User.Read.All` and `UserAuthenticationMethod.Read.All` consented |
